title: Charles Dickens 200th Anniversary Collection Vol. 4
creator: Charles Dickens
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of Charles Dickens 200th Anniversary Collection Vol. 4. Read by volunteer readers. This year is the 200th anniversary of Dickens' birth. This is the fourth volume; the first volume of short works - fiction, essays, poetry and speeches, previously unrecorded for LibriVox, was catalogued by Dickens' birthday on February 7th 2012. Further volumes will follow during the anniversary year. (Summary by Ruth Golding) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
